The paper deals with an algorithmic problem related to trees, which is a fundamental data structure in computer science. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is the most likely sub-category. The problem involves computing a maximum induced matching width, which is a geometric property of the tree, so cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also a likely sub-category. The algorithmic approach involves sorting and divide-and-conquer techniques, which are common in cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DL (Digital Libraries). Finally, the paper mentions the concept of "optimal layout", which could be related to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
